    "title": "NSDL Asia Pacific Associates is Hiring: Credit Analyst (Mid-Level)",
    "description": "We at NSDL Asia Pacific Associates are looking for an experienced Credit Analyst based out of Vijayawada. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout NSDL Asia Pacific Associates:\nNSDL Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Sc / M.Sc in Life Sciences\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n• Proficiency in Power BI\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in Risk Management\n• Proficiency in Financial Reporting\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vijayawada, Andhra Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with NSDL Asia Pacific Associates!",
